The paper deals with streaming algorithms for recognizing well-parenthesized expressions with errors, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of the Hamming Distance problem, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses the space and time complexity of the algorithms, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and formal languages (cs.FL).
